<p>The U.S. military carried out another strike on an alleged narco-trafficking vessel in the eastern Pacific on Wednesday, Defense Secretary Pete Hegseth announced on X, saying four people were killed and the operation occurred in international waters . Officials and released video showed a small craft erupting in a large explosion; the Pentagon described the operation as part of an ongoing campaign against maritime drug trafficking that has run for weeks . Reporting places the wider death toll from the U.S. campaign in recent weeks at roughly 61â€“62 people, depending on outlets&#x27; counts, and the White House asserted links to a designated terrorist group without publicly providing supporting evidence, according to some outlets .</p><img src='https://kagiproxy.com/img/LBxg7ZD5obhb5Fh5X5Zcsy3X08000drH_0oaSI5D1HmE5qtNUqjbc2R7uBke1Lg04AXv-Modm3S6OXwlelJTXbsYkg6Pt-P9nDegC84G_zjGiNpgg0vg_d0usJ-kNDvHMo4cgNgIHbjZ4ubFnbZiSZw1eos5pKVEDUmvQohqLiS2mr6zJoWMVYlZcHG7ufsdFg9CMZSsYJqAhUOFBqAvONUTYklNLCAGK97gC3vlzD-F' alt='Image released with reporting on the strike: US hits another alleged drug boat in Pacific, killing 4 people' /><br /><h3>Highlights:</h3><ul><li>Campaign scale: Pentagon officials described the latest action as the 15th strike in the maritime anti-narcotics campaign, reflecting sustained operations since September .</li><li>Recent escalation: The newest hit came two days after what reporting described as the deadliest set of strikes in the weekslong campaign, signaling a recent uptick in lethal operations .</li><li>No U.S. casualties: Officials said the strike occurred in international waters and that no U.S. forces were harmed during the operation, according to press accounts .</li><li>Announcement context: Defense Secretary Pete Hegseth posted video of the strike on X while traveling abroad, using social media to publicize the action during a diplomatic trip, per reporting .</li></ul><blockquote>Transiting along a known narco-trafficking route, and carrying narcotics. - Pete Hegseth</blockquote><h3>Perspectives:</h3><ul><li>U.S. Department of Defense (Pete Hegseth): The Pentagon said the vessel was identified by intelligence as moving along known narco-trafficking routes and that the strike targeted suspected narcotics trafficking . (<a href='https://www.theglobeandmail.com/world/article-us-military-drug-boat-pacific-hegseth-trump/'>The Globe and Mail</a>)</li><li>Al Jazeera (reporting): Al Jazeera reported that the White House claimed the vessel was operated by a &#x27;designated terrorist organisation&#x27; but noted officials did not provide supporting evidence in the reporting . (<a href='https://www.aljazeera.com/news/2025/10/30/us-says-it-killed-four-terrorists-in-latest-strike-on-alleged-drug-vessel'>Al Jazeera</a>)</li><li>The Globe and Mail (analysis): Coverage described the administration&#x27;s maritime campaign as divisive in regional waters off South America, reflecting debate over the approach . (<a href='https://www.theglobeandmail.com/world/article-us-military-drug-boat-pacific-hegseth-trump/'>The Globe and Mail</a>)</li></ul><h3>Sources:</h3><ul><li><a href='https://www.cbsnews.com/news/trump-administration-strikes-another-alleged-drug-boat-pacific-killing-4/'>Trump administration says it struck another alleged drug boat, killing 4</a> - cbsnews.com</li><li><a href='https://www.scmp.com/news/world/americas/article/3330834/us-says-strike-another-alleged-drug-boat-pacific-kills-4'>US says strike on another alleged drug boat in Pacific kills 4</a> - scmp.com</li><li><a href='https://www.firstpost.com/world/us-hits-another-alleged-drug-boat-in-pacific-killing-4-people-13946296.html'>US hits another alleged drug boat in Pacific, killing 4 people</a> - firstpost.com</li><li><a href='https://www.nytimes.com/2025/10/29/us/politics/military-drug-boat-strikes.html'>U.S. Military Kills Four More People Accused of Smuggling Drugs on Boats</a> - nytimes.com</li><li><a href='https://www.ndtv.com/world-news/4-killed